## 6. Rollback Procedures

### 6.1 Frontend Rollback (Vercel)

1. Go to Vercel Dashboard > Deployments
2. Find previous working deployment
3. Click "..." menu > "Promote to Production"
4. Vercel will redeploy that version

### 6.2 Backend Rollback

**If using Vercel**:
- Same as frontend: promote previous deployment

**If using Railway/Render**:
- Redeploy previous Git commit
- Or use platform's rollback feature

### 6.3 Database Rollback

**Supabase**:
- Use Supabase Dashboard > Database > Backups
- Restore from backup if available
- Or manually revert schema changes via SQL

**Warning**: Database rollbacks can cause data loss. Always backup before major changes.

---

## Quick Reference: Deployment Commands

```bash
# ===== BACKEND DEPLOYMENT =====
cd backend

# Create requirements.txt if not exists
pip freeze > requirements.txt

# Deploy to Vercel (if root dir is backend)
vercel --prod

# Or deploy via Railway
railway up


# ===== FRONTEND DEPLOYMENT =====
cd ckb-tracker

# Build check
npm run build

# Deploy to Vercel (if root dir is ckb-tracker)
vercel --prod

# Or push to Git and let Vercel auto-deploy
git add .
git commit -m "Deploy to production"
git push origin main


# ===== VERIFY DEPLOYMENT =====
# Frontend
curl https://your-frontend.vercel.app

# Backend
curl https://your-backend.vercel.app/
```

---

## Troubleshooting Common Issues

### Issue: "CORS error" in production
**Solution**: Update `CORS_ORIGINS` in backend environment variables to include production frontend URL.

### Issue: "Supabase connection failed"
**Solution**: 
1. Verify `DATABASE_URL` is correct
2. Check Supabase project is active
3. Ensure IP is not blocked in Supabase (Settings > Database > Connection pooling)

### Issue: "Build failed" on Vercel
**Solution**:
1. Check build logs in Vercel dashboard
2. Verify all environment variables are set
3. Test build locally with `npm run build`

### Issue: "Environment variables not loading"
**Solution**:
1. Redeploy after adding environment variables
2. For Next.js, ensure vars are prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` to expose to browser
3. Check Vercel dashboard > Settings > Environment Variables

---

## Security Reminders

⚠️ **Before Going Live**:
- [ ] Change all default passwords and keys
- [ ] Enable Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) on sensitive tables
- [ ] Set `COOKIE_SECURE=True` in production
- [ ] Restrict CORS origins to your domain only
- [ ] Remove any test/seed data from production
- [ ] Enable rate limiting (already configured via slowapi)
- [ ] Set up monitoring and alerting

---

## Final Deployment Checklist

Print this and check off before going live:

- [ ] All environment variables configured in Vercel
- [ ] Supabase database schema created
- [ ] Backend deployed and responding at production URL
- [ ] Frontend deployed and loading at production URL
- [ ] User registration works
- [ ] User login works
- [ ] Dashboard displays data
- [ ] No console errors in browser
- [ ] CORS properly configured
- [ ] HTTPS enforced (Vercel does this automatically)
- [ ] Custom domain configured (optional)
- [ ] Supabase RLS enabled
- [ ] Monitoring/Logging set up
- [ ] Team notified of deployment
- [ ] Rollback plan tested

